Handwritten Digit Classification using ANN ✍️🔢
This project uses an Artificial Neural Network (ANN) to classify handwritten digits from the popular MNIST dataset.

📦 Dataset
Source: MNIST Dataset
60,000 training images & 10,000 test images
Grayscale 28x28 images representing digits 0–9

🛠️ Preprocessing
Normalized pixel values (0–255 scaled to 0–1)
Train-test split handled by keras.datasets.mnist

🧠 Model Architecture
Framework: TensorFlow/Keras
Model: Sequential ANN

Layers:
Flatten input layer (28x28 → 784)
Dense layer with 128 neurons (ReLU)
Dense layer with 32 neurons (ReLU)
Output layer with 10 neurons (Softmax)

⚙️ Training
Loss Function: Sparse Categorical Crossentropy
Optimizer: Adam
Epochs: 25
Validation: 20% split from training data

✅ Results
Final Test Accuracy: 97.93%
Model correctly predicts handwritten digits with high precision

🧪 Prediction Example
Model correctly classified a sample image as: 7
